16/04/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The foreign ministry opened the country's first diplomatic academy on Thursday (15 April) in Tirana. Established in co-operation with the Italian government, the course programme is based on Rome's Mario Toscano Diplomatic Institute. At the opening ceremony, Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami described the academy as an important development in Albanian diplomacy. (ATA - 15/04/04)
